(41, 13, 35, 41, 6, 48, 48, NULL, 'Watches of the Night', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of time during the night, specifically referencing different watches. Mark 13:35 mentions the uncertainty of the master''s arrival at various times, while Mark 6:48 specifies the fourth watch of the night when Jesus approaches the disciples.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
