(41, 14, 1, 3, 23, 5, 7, 'feast of the passover', 'Connection of Passover Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the Passover, with Mark referencing the timing of the feast and the plot against Jesus, while Leviticus outlines the observance of the Passover and the feast of unleavened bread. This connection highlights the importance of these events in the biblical narrative.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
